extends Dictionary
    Some categories of objects in a PDF file can be referred to by name rather than by object reference. The correspondence between names and objects is established by the document’s name dictionary (PDF 1.2), located by means of the Names entry in the document’s catalog (see 7.7.2, "Document Catalog"). Each entry in this dictionary designates the root of a name tree (see 7.9.6, "Name Trees") defining names for a particular category of objects.
